deleteCellPad(25.10)                                      deleteCellPad(25.10)

Name
       deleteCellPad - Deletes the padding for a cell or list of cells

Syntax
       deleteCellPad

       [-help]

       <cellNames>

       Deletes  the  padding for a cell or list of cells. If a regular expres-
       sion or a list of cells is provided, this command returns the number of
       cells for which the padding was deleted.

Parameters
       <cellNames>
              Specifies the cell name for which padding has to be deleted. The
              cell name can be a regular expression, or a list of  cell  names
              or expressions.

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each deleteCellPad parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man deleteCellPad.

Examples
              * The following command deletes padding for the cells with  pre-
                fix FF_SCAN:

                deleteCellPad FF_SCAN*

              * The  following command deletes padding for all cells that have
                names starting with BUF, INV, and DLY. If a matched cell  name
                does  not  have padding information, it is ignored without any
                message.

                deleteCellPad {BUF* INV* DLY*}

              * The following command deletes padding for  cell  FF_SCAN1  and
                cell FF_SCAN2:

                deleteCellPad {FF_SCAN1 FF_SCAN2}

Related Information
              * reportCellPad

              * specifyCellPad

